==English==
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#{{UK}} (''rare, taboo slang'') Singular of '''[[bollocks]]''' in the sense of "testicles".
#:''You've got a bollock hanging out of your shorts.''

====Usage notes====
*In the sense of "testicle", the more common form is "one of my/your (etc) bollocks".

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

#{{UK}} (''transitive, taboo slang'') To [[reprimand]] severely.
#:''The boss '''bollocked''' me for coming in late.''

It's also known to be slang for clergymen. Read the "Nevermind the Bollocks" court case article here: ww.acc.umu.se/~samhain/summerofhate/courtcase.html I had to remove a "W"

